NAME
       ldns_str2period - converts a ttl value (like 5d2h) to a long

SYNOPSIS
       #include <stdint.h>
       #include <stdbool.h>

       #include <ldns/ldns.h>

       uint32_t ldns_str2period(const char *nptr, const char **endptr);

DESCRIPTION
       ldns_str2period() converts a ttl value (like 5d2h) to a long.
              nptr: the start of the string
              endptr: points to the last char in case of error
              Returns the convert duration value

